1. 153.6 million individuals have been affected by these leaks
2. Link to chart: https://infogr.am/w3u8jOnm4pvviqGq
3. Going by the numbers, there have been 480 leaks of paper records, and 956 leaks of electronic records. Thus, electronics records have certainly been leaked more number of times.
4. However, we know that far more records are available electronically than on paper. Thus, the chance that an electronic record is leaked is higher. What we need to see is what percentage of total records are leaked for both paper and electronic. Only then can we say if electronic records tend to get breached more.